1 Tomato
250 g Beef Mince
1 sachet Brown Mustard Seeds
1 packet Mayonnaise
1 packet Onion Chutney
1 Cucumber
1 packet Fine Breadcrumbs
1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves
1 sachet Mumbai Spice Blend
2 packet Potato
1 drizzle olive oil
1 piece egg
1 drizzle white wine vinegar

• Cut potato into fries.
• Set your air fryer to 200°C. Place fries into the air
fryer basket, drizzle with olive oil, season with
salt, sprinkle over brown mustard seeds and
toss to coat. Cook for 10 minutes. Shake the
basket, then cook until golden, a further
10-15 minutes. Divide between serving plates.
TIP: No air fryer? Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C
fan-forced. Place fries on a lined oven tray. Drizzle
with olive oil, season with salt, sprinkle over brown
mustard seeds and toss to coat. Bake until tender,
20-25 minutes.

• Finely chop garlic.
• Roughly chop tomato and slice cucumber
into rounds.

• In a medium bowl, combine beef mince,
Mumbai spice blend, a pinch of salt, fine
breadcrumbs, garlic and the egg.
• Using damp hands, shape heaped spoonfuls of
the beef mixture into small meatballs
(4-5 per person). Transfer to a plate.
Little cooks: Join the fun by helping combine the
ingredients and shaping the mixture into meatballs!
Make sure to wash your hands well afterwards.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil
over a medium-high heat. Cook meatballs,
turning, until browned and cooked through,
8-10 minutes (cook in batches if your pan is
getting crowded).
• Remove the pan from heat, then add onion
chutney and a splash of water, tossing
meatballs to coat.

• Meanwhile, in a second medium bowl, combine
mixed salad leaves, tomato, cucumber, a pinch
of salt and pepper and a drizzle of white wine
vinegar and olive oil.
Little cooks: Take the lead by tossing the salad!

• Divide fragrant beef meatballs, spiced fries and
mixed salad between plates.
• Serve with mayonnaise. Enjoy!